         <abstract>
            <p>A new way of estimating local discretization errors (based on an idea due to P. E. Zadunaisky) is introduced. If error estimates obtained by this method are used in connection with the general class of iterated deferred correction algorithms, they lead to an extension of the domain of applicability, when compared with the variants used by Fox and Pereyra.</p>
          </abstract>
